correctness.rationale: The extraction is largely incorrect and not traceable to the article in many places, with multiple schema/semantic issues. Key problems: (1) Process parameters are largely guessed or misassigned: temperature 200 °C corresponds to ALD Al2O3 (not the IGZO PEALD temperature, which is not reported); plasmaPower 100 W is stated for SiO2 deposition only, not for IGZO; reactor pressure, dosingTime, purgeTime, flowRates, saturation, nucleationPeriod are not reported in the paper; deliveryMethod is incorrectly filled with “conventional photolithography and wet etching” (not an ALD delivery method). (2) Thickness control values are inconsistent and ungrounded: GPC=0.1 Å and numberofCycles=200 would give ~2 nm, not the reported 20 nm; only the 20 nm filmThickness is supported. (3) SupercycleDesign is invalid: compounds are listed as “InGaZnO” instead of separate subcycles (e.g., In2O3/Ga2O3/ZnO), counts include a non-integer 1.3 (physically impossible), and it conflates the reported cation ratio (2:1:1.3) with subcycle counts; subcycleSequence is nonsensical. (4) Reactant selection is partly misrepresented: precursors are tied to “InGaZnO” instead of mapping DADI to In, TMGa to Ga, DEZ to Zn; carrierGas and purgingGas are not given in the article. (5) Material properties are mostly invented: refractive index, absorption coefficient, band gap, resistivity, carrier density, uniformity, conformality, roughness, and film density are not reported; “Hall measurements” are not used; filmDensity unit/value are unrealistic. ElementalConcentration=1% is erroneous; the paper does report a cation ratio (2:1:1.3) and hydrogen contents (e.g., IGZO ~8.9%), which are not correctly captured. (6) Device properties: field-effect mobility, Vth, and SS correspond to device E and are plausible, but SS uses the wrong unit/value (should be 0.24 V/dec ≈ 240 mV, not 0.24 mV); on/off ratio is not reported. (7) Minor: substrate (glass), IGZO by PEALD, co-reactant Ar/O2 plasma, 20 nm IGZO thickness, device structure (top-gate staggered), and cation ratio 2:1:1.3 are aligned. To correct, remove or mark unknown all unreported parameters (pressure, times, flows, nucleation, saturation), fix deliveryMethod, set temperature/plasmaPower only if explicitly given for IGZO, correct SS to 240 mV, represent supercycle per-element with integer counts (or omit if not reported), map precursors to In/Ga/Zn subcycles, and revise material properties to only include values traceable to the article (e.g., cation ratio, amorphous phase if supported).

completeness.rationale: Major incompleteness and low traceability. The article reports multiple ALD processes (IGZO by PEALD; SiO2 by PEALD using DIPAS and Ar/O2 plasma at 250 °C, 100 W; Al2O3 by ALD using TMA/H2O at 200 °C; plus a stacked GI with an additional 20 nm Al2O3), but only a single IGZO process is extracted. Many provided parameters are not reported in the article and lack traceability (pressure, dosing/purge times, flow rates, saturation, nucleation period, GPC, number of cycles, uniformity, conformality, refractive index, absorption coefficient, band gap, resistivity, carrier density, roughness, film density, on/off ratio, film stability, reproducibility). Several values are incorrect or misassigned: plasma power 100 W applies to SiO2 ALD, not IGZO; temperature 200 °C corresponds to Al2O3 ALD, not IGZO; deliveryMethod is misused (photolithography is not a precursor delivery method); carrier/purging gases are not specified in the article; supercycleDesign is improperly modeled (compound listed as InGaZnO instead of In2O3, Ga2O3, ZnO; counts include 1.3 without a defined supercycle strategy; subcycleSequence lacks the three sub-oxides). Units/values errors include subthreshold swing reported as 0.24 mV (should be 0.24 V/dec; per schema it should be 240 mV) and nonsensical elementalConcentration (1%) and filmDensity units. While some items match (substrate: glass; IGZO thickness 20 nm; IGZO composition ratio In:Ga:Zn = 2:1:1.3; device structure; mobility and Vth for device E), the extraction omits the separate ALD processes for SiO2 and Al2O3 and adds numerous ungrounded values, violating completeness and traceability. To improve: add separate process objects for SiO2 (DIPAS + Ar/O2 plasma, 250 °C, 100 W) and Al2O3 (TMA + H2O, 200 °C); correct IGZO parameters to only what is reported (PEALD, precursors DADI/TMGa/DEZ, Ar/O2 plasma, 20 nm thickness, glass substrate); properly model supercycleDesign with subcycles for In2O3, Ga2O3, ZnO using the 2:1:1.3 ratio; remove fabricated timings/flows/pressures unless reported; fix SS unit to 240 mV to comply with schema; remove or justify optical/electrical film properties and other aspects not in the article.
